Class KeyTypeManager.KeyFactory<KeyFormatProtoT extends com.google.protobuf.MessageLite,KeyProtoT extends com.google.protobuf.MessageLite>

    public abstract static class KeyTypeManager.KeyFactory<KeyFormatProtoT extends com.google.protobuf.MessageLite,KeyProtoT extends com.google.protobuf.MessageLite>
extends Object
    A KeyFactory creates new keys from a given KeyFormat.

    A KeyFactory implements all the methods which are required if a KeyTypeManager should also be able to generate keys. In particular, in this case it needs to have some KeyFormat protocol buffer which can be validated, parsed, and from which a key can be generated.
